Since you're moving from C++ to Go, you're moving from manual control to a garbage-collected environment. AI is great at the "surface" translation—turning a C++ loop into a Go loop—but it will struggle with the architectural implications. For example, if the C++ game uses heavy pointer arithmetic or custom memory pools for performance, the AI might suggest Go code that is syntactically correct but creates massive GC pressure, effectively killing the game's framerate.

